Usage: get_lib_arcs [-help] [-filter <expr>] [-quiet] { [ [-from <from_lib_pins>] [-to <to_lib_pins>] ] | -of_objects < lib_cell_list | timing_arcs > }

-help                     # Prints out the command usage
-filter <expr>            # Filters the collection with the specified
                          # expression (string, optional)
-from <from_lib_pins>     # Creates a collection of all library arcs that
                          # originate from the specified library pins
                          # (string, optional)
-of_objects < lib_cell_list | timing_arcs >
                          # Creates a collection of all library arcs that are
                          # associated with the specified library cells or
                          # timing arcs (string, optional)
-quiet                    # Suppresses all error and warning messages generated
                          # when the get_lib_arcs command is run (bool, optional)
-to <to_lib_pins>         # Creates a collection of all library arcs that
                          # terminate at the specified library pins
                          # (string, optional)